UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'Although most of the United States is located on the North American continent, parts of Alaska are in Asia.  These parts of Alaska are separated from mainland Russia by the Bering Strait, a body of water that is only about 53 miles wide at its narrowest point. For centuries, Indigenous people from both sides of the Bering Strait traveled between Alaska and Russia.  They have used a variety of methods to cross the strait, including kayaks, dog sleds, and snowmobiles. What’s the most likely reason for the author to include the details about the Bering Strait?',
